Put the repo on the ticket branch, cut from the latest base branch (`{{git.baseBranch}}`):

- Derive the branch name from the ticket id `{{arg}}`: lowercase the id and add a 2–4 word slug, following `{{git.branchPattern}}` (e.g. `{{eg.prefixUpper}}-312` → `{{eg.prefixLower}}-312-add-login`).
- If a branch for {{arg}} already exists, check it out instead of creating one — look for a local or remote branch whose name starts with the lowercased ticket id (`git branch --list` and `git branch -r`).
- If the working tree has uncommitted changes that belong to another ticket, stop and ask — never stash silently or carry another ticket's work onto this branch.
- Otherwise: `git fetch origin` then `git checkout -b <branch> origin/{{git.baseBranch}}`.
- Report the branch name and its base commit.
